Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_proto_timing_settings(25.10)              set_proto_timing_settings(25.10)

Name
       set_proto_timing_settings

Syntax
        set_proto_timing_settings

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       Sets  or  resets  the  prototyping  settings in the flow. The following
       variables are set by the command:

              * setInputTransitionDelay 80.0psps

                (Default:250.0ps)

              * setDefaultNetLoad 0.0pf

                (Default: 0.1pf)

              * setDefaultNetDelay 0ns

                (Default: 2.5ns)

              * setUseDefaultDelayLimit 0

                (Default: 300)

              * setDelayCalMode -enable_high_fanout true

                (Default: false)

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each set_proto-timing_settings parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man set_proto-timing_settings.

       -reset Resets all prototyping settings. The settings are enabled by de-
              fault.

              It  resets the variables mentioned above and rebuilds the timing
              graph. It also resets the following setting:

              setDelayCalMode -ignoreNetLoad false

              The above is set to true by timeDesign -proto, and must  be  re-
              set.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Related Information
              *

                set_proto_model

              *

                Prototyping Methodologies chapter in the Innovus User Guide

